"""
dN/dS Pipeline: Pairwise synonymous and non-synonymous substitution rate
estimation between two species.

Three input modes — set in config/config.yaml:

  Mode A — genome + GFF (full pipeline):
    query:
      fasta: path/to/species1.fasta
      gff:   path/to/species1.gff
      prefix: species1

  Mode B — pre-made FAA + FNA (skip Anchorwave & transeq entirely):
    query:
      faa: path/to/species1.faa
      fna: path/to/species1.fna
      prefix: species1

  Mode C — CDS nucleotide FNA only (transeq runs, Anchorwave skipped):
    query:
      fna: path/to/species1.fna
      prefix: species1

All modes are detected automatically and can be mixed per species.
Priority when multiple keys are present: Mode B > Mode C > Mode A.

Tool switches — set in config/config.yaml under tools:
  cds_extraction: anchorwave | gffread   (Mode A only)
  search_method:  blast | diamond        (all modes)
  trimmer:        gblocks | trimal       (all modes)

Output structure:
  intermediate/
    cds/           CDS nucleotide and protein sequences (Modes A and C)
    blast/         Search databases, forward and reverse results
    rbh_pairs.tsv  Filtered RBH gene pair list (query TAB target)
    input/         Per-gene-pair FAA and FNA files
    aligns/        MAFFT, pal2nal, and trimmed alignments
    codeml/        Per-gene codeml output directories
  results/
    dnds_output.tsv                      Final dN/dS table
    plots/dnds_boxplot.pdf                Boxplot of dN, dS, dN/dS
    plots/dnds_violin.pdf                 Violin plot of dN, dS, dN/dS
    plots/dnds_scatter.pdf                dN vs dS scatter
    plots/functional_summary.pdf          Gene category bar chart
    plots/pseudogene_evidence.pdf         Pseudogene evidence chart
    tables/genes_conserved.tsv            ω < 0.5
    tables/genes_relaxed.tsv              0.5 ≤ ω < 1
    tables/genes_degenerate.tsv           ω ≥ 1
    tables/genes_degenerate_annotated.tsv ω ≥ 1 + sequence evidence
    tables/genes_undefined_ds.tsv         dS = 0
    tables/genes_high_dn.tsv              dN above median
    tables/genes_high_ds.tsv              dS above median
    tables/genes_high_dnds.tsv            dN/dS above median
    tables/genes_above_diagonal.tsv       dN > dS
    tables/genes_on_diagonal.tsv          dN ≈ dS (±10%)
    tables/genes_below_diagonal.tsv       dN < dS

Steps:
  [Mode A only]
  1. Extract CDS (extract_cds.py — anchorwave or gffread)
  2. Sanitise headers (clean_fna.py)
  [Modes A and C]
  3. Translate to protein (fix_transeq.py — EMBOSS transeq)
  [All modes]
  4. Reciprocal Best Hits (get_rbh.py — blast or diamond)
  5. Extract per-gene-pair FAA and FNA (extract_gene_pair.py)
  6. Protein alignment (MAFFT)
  7. Codon alignment (pal2nal)
  8. Alignment trimming (run_trimmer.py — gblocks or trimal)
  9. dN/dS estimation (run_codeml.py — PAML codeml pairwise mode -2)
  10. Parse and collate results (collate_results.py)
  11. Visualisation and functional classification (plot_results.py)
  12. Pseudogene sequence evidence check (check_pseudogenes.py)
"""

# =============================================================================
# Author:  Suvratha Jayaprasad
# Contact: https://suvrathaprasad.github.io/index.html
